==Finnish==

===Deverbal suffix===
'''-u''' (''with back vowel harmony'')
'''-y''' (''with front vowel harmony'')

# Used to form nouns, usually, from verbs whose [[citation form]] ends with ''-ea'', ''-eä'', ''-ia'' or ''-iä''.
#: [[hyppiä]] ''to be jumping'' -&gt; [[hyppy]] ''jump''
#: [[itkeä]] ''to cry'' -&gt; [[itku]] ''cry(ing)''
#: [[potkia]] ''to kick'' -&gt; [[potku]] ''kick''

[[Category:Finnish suffixes|u]]

==Esperanto==
===Suffix===
'''-u'''

# do [it]! (Ending of the [[imperative]] in verbs.)
#: Speculative etymology: from Hebrew imperative suffix ''[[-û]]'', the [u] sound of Greek imperative inflection of deponent verbs, or both.
#* ''[[paroli|Parolu]]!'': [[speak|Speak]]!
# -one. (Ending of the individual [[:Category:Esperanto correlatives|correlatives]].)
#* ''[[kiu]]'': what '''individual''', [[who]]
#* ''[[tiu]]'': that '''individual''', that one
#* ''[[ĉiu]]'': all '''individuals''', [[everyone]]
#* ''[[iu]]'': some '''individual''', [[someone]]
#* ''[[neniu]]'': no '''individual''', [[nobody]]

